================================================================================
       UBUNTU 22.04 TO 24.04 LTS UPGRADE - ANNOUNCEMENT & GUIDE
================================================================================

Hi All,

We are pleased to announce a shell script based automation solution for
in-place OS upgrades in the Ubuntu space. This automation helps in performing
end-to-end Ubuntu 22.04 LTS to 24.04 LTS in-place upgrades including
pre-upgrade health checks, upgrade execution, post-upgrade validation,
and cleanup.


================================================================================
WHAT IS THIS AUTOMATION ABOUT?
================================================================================

The primary objective of this automation is to automate the in-place upgrade
of servers from Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (Jammy) to Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (Noble Numbat).
It collects information about the system state, performs pre-upgrade checks,
patches the OS to the latest 22.04 packages, executes the upgrade via
do-release-upgrade, then runs post-upgrade cleanup and validation to ensure
services are running correctly. There are two scripts:
  - Script 1 runs the upgrade (30-60 mins)
  - Script 2 runs cleanup and reboot after the upgrade completes.


================================================================================
BEFORE YOU START - THINGS TO KNOW
================================================================================

  - Scripts connect to servers over SSH and run commands remotely.
  - You need sudo/root access on the target servers.
  - The upgrade takes 30-60+ minutes per server.
  - The server will reboot at the end of Script 2.
  - Test on ONE server first before running on multiple servers.
  - Ensure you have console/out-of-band access in case SSH breaks
    during the upgrade.

  NOTE: Replace all placeholder values ("123", "svc_123", Foreman URL)
  with your actual environment details before running either script.


================================================================================
USE CASES
================================================================================

  1. Pre-Upgrade Health Checks:
     Validates system state before upgrade - including OS version (must be
     22.04), disk space (minimum 5-10 GB free), broken packages, and
     running services.

  2. Automated Upgrade Execution:
     Backs up repo sources, patches to latest 22.04, configures the LTS
     upgrade channel, then launches do-release-upgrade in non-interactive
     background mode with full logging.

  3. Post-Upgrade Validation:
     After upgrade, verifies the OS version is Ubuntu 24.04, checks for
     failed services and broken packages, and confirms disk space is healthy.

  4. Internal Repo Restore:
     Re-points the server to your organisation's internal Foreman/Pulp
     Noble (24.04) package mirrors and removes stale Jammy repo references.

  5. Cleanup & Reboot:
     Cleans up old disabled repo files, re-enables the Kubernetes repo,
     refreshes apt package lists, and reboots the server to load the
     new kernel.


================================================================================
ADVANTAGE
================================================================================

  1. Time Efficiency:
     Manual in-place upgrades typically take 90-180 minutes per server with
     human oversight. This script reduces active effort and can run
     unattended overnight.

  2. Consistency:
     Ensures a standardised, repeatable approach across all servers and
     eliminates human errors such as missed steps or incorrect repo
     configurations.

  3. Scalability:
     The scripts accept a list of servers and loop through them sequentially.
     Running against large environments is an added advantage over manual
     per-server work.

  4. Healthy Environment:
     Pre- and post-upgrade checks ensure the server is in a valid state at
     every stage. Issues are caught and logged before they cause incidents.


